{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487020","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487020"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T02:54:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T02:54:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"234"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"234","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/234"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.12,0.66,0.07,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"234"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107369"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"234","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/234"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"234"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89855"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"1110"},{"type":"tags","id":"1179"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"515"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11249"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107369","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107369"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 54-year-old man presents with a painless abdominal swelling two months after undergoing a laparotomy and sigmoid colectomy for a T3 N1 M0 carcinoma. His recovery from the procedure was uneventful. His medical history includes type 2 diabetes and a laparoscopic appendicectomy as a teenager. His medications include metformin. He has a 20 pack-year smoking history and drinks three glasses of wine a day. On examination, his pulse rate is 80/min, blood pressure 130/90 mmHg and BMI 34 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2.\u003C/sup\u003E His abdomen is soft and there is a 4 cm reducible swelling at the midpoint of his otherwise well-healed abdominal wound from his recent surgery.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is most likely to have been the major contributory factor to his current problem?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The previous appendicectomy","The smoking history","His BMI","The diabetes","His alcohol consumption"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe patient has an incisional hernia. There are many risk factors for the development of such hernias and these include obesity, liver disease, smoking, old age and malnutrition. In this patient, whilst his diabetes could be a contributing factor, his obesity - shown with a \u003Cstrong\u003EBMI\u003C/strong\u003E of 34 - is almost certainly the major contributing risk factor for his incisional hernia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmoking \u003C/strong\u003Eis a risk factor, but in this case a less likely problem compared with his obesity. \u003Cstrong\u003EAlcohol abuse \u003C/strong\u003Eis not known a risk factor for incisional hernia. Although an \u003Cstrong\u003Eappendicectomy\u003C/strong\u003E could cause an incisional hernia, laparoscopic surgeries are less likely to cause incisional hernias than open surgeries, and it would expected to be at the site of the laparoscopic incisions, not at the site of the recent surgical site wound.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Obesity is a common cause of long-term abdominal wound failure."],"references":["Itatsu K, Yokoyama Y, Sugawara G, Kubota H, Tojima Y, Kurumiya Y, et al. Incidence of and risk factors for incisional hernia after abdominal surgery. Br J Surg. 2014;101(11):1439-47. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25123379/","Fischer JP, Basta MN, Mirzabeigi MN, et al. A Risk Model and Cost Analysis of Incisional Hernia After Elective Abdominal Surgery Based on 12,373 Cases. Ann Surg 2016; 263:1010-17"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89855"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"234"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89855","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89855"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-29T10:47:24+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-29T10:47:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"234"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107369"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Investigations","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"1110","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1110"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Distended abdomen","synonyms":["Swollen abdomen","Abdominal bloating","Abdominal distension","Abdominal distention","Abdominal swelling","Bloating"],"descri